<i>the third in as many weeks,</i>
<i>and the sixth in the last two months.</i>

957
01:16:50,272 --> 01:16:53,901
We have all the evidence we need.
We'll have closure very soon.

958
01:16:54,009 --> 01:16:57,035
[ Sobbing ]

959
01:16:57,146 --> 01:16:59,046
<i>[ Doorbell Rings ]</i>

960
01:16:59,148 --> 01:17:01,946
[ Martin ] Yeah, I'd like to speak
to the duty doctor.

961
01:17:02,051 --> 01:17:03,951
<i>[ Woman ]</i>
<i>One moment.</i>

962
01:17:04,053 --> 01:17:05,953
- [ Doctor] Hello?
- Yeah, hello.

963
01:17:06,055 --> 01:17:10,856
This is Martin Bells. You know,
the screwed-up kid from Forensics.

964
01:17:10,960 --> 01:17:14,054
-Joyce asked me to say hello.
- Who?

965
01:17:14,163 --> 01:17:17,826
Joyce--your playmate.

966
01:17:17,933 --> 01:17:21,198
Listen. I have personally asked
for your removal.

967
01:17:21,303 --> 01:17:25,137
- Go home.
- Well, I thought you'd want me to stay.

968
01:17:25,241 --> 01:17:27,971
Go and see
a psychiatrist.

969
01:17:28,077 --> 01:17:29,977
Do you think
I'm a psychopath?

970
01:17:30,079 --> 01:17:32,274
Well, you wouldn't be the first
night watchman who was.

971
01:17:32,381 --> 01:17:34,281
[ Dial Tone ]

972
01:17:41,390 --> 01:17:43,290
"The first."

973
01:17:45,027 --> 01:17:46,927
"The first."

974
01:17:48,330 --> 01:17:50,230
Deputy Inspector
Bill Davies, Homicide.

975
01:17:50,332 --> 01:17:52,493
- I'd like to speak
to Martin Bells, please.
- Yeah, well, Martin's not here.

976
01:17:52,601 --> 01:17:54,967
- I'm afraid we don't know where he is.
<i>- [ Phone Rings ]</i>

977
01:17:55,070 --> 01:17:57,766
- Hello.
- Yeah, hi. It's me.

978
01:17:57,873 --> 01:18:00,398
Martin,Joyce
has been murdered.

979
01:18:00,509 --> 01:18:02,841
The cops are here
looking for you right now.

980
01:18:02,945 --> 01:18:05,311
- I'm going over there.
- I'm afraid that's too dangerous.

981
01:18:05,414 --> 01:18:08,645
- He didn't do it!
- Keep your ears open.
I'm gonna try something.

982
01:18:08,751 --> 01:18:10,981
<i>[ Katherine ]</i>
<i>Martin is not a murderer.</i>

983
01:18:11,086 --> 01:18:12,986
<i>[ Davies ]</i>
<i>We don't make up the evidence.</i>

984
01:18:13,088 --> 01:18:15,454
He's a suspect because weird things
happened at work?

985
01:18:15,558 --> 01:18:17,822
[ Sighs ]

986
01:18:17,927 --> 01:18:21,658
[ Davies ] Listen. She exposed
him herself, okay?

987
01:18:21,764 --> 01:18:24,028
- She wrote his name.
- What did she write?

988
01:18:24,133 --> 01:18:26,363
- His name.
- Yeah, but what name?

989
01:18:31,507 --> 01:18:35,773
- Martin.
- No. No. We changed the names.

990
01:18:35,878 --> 01:18:40,110
<i>Joyce thought he was James, so if it</i>
<i>was him, she would have written "James. "</i>

991
01:18:40,216 --> 01:18:43,845
- Well, that makes you our
prime suspect then, doesn't it?
<i>- [ Marie ] This is ridiculous.</i>

992
01:18:43,953 --> 01:18:47,411
<i>No.</i>
<i>There was no name.</i>

993
01:18:47,523 --> 01:18:49,514
<i>[ Davies ]</i>
<i>What?</i>

994
01:18:49,625 --> 01:18:53,721
- Katherine was there.
- You were there?

995
01:18:53,829 --> 01:18:57,458
<i>- When?</i>
- There was a lot of blood.

996
01:18:57,566 --> 01:18:59,727
But there was
no name.

997
01:19:01,203 --> 01:19:03,433
And the murderer...

998
01:19:03,539 --> 01:19:05,530
was still there.

999
01:19:07,309 --> 01:19:09,209
What?

1000
01:19:09,311 --> 01:19:11,745
Katherine.

1001
01:19:13,249 --> 01:19:17,345
[ Line Ringing ]

1002
01:19:17,453 --> 01:19:19,353
[ Man ]
Hello.

1003
01:19:19,455 --> 01:19:23,755
Yeah, hello?
This is Martin Bells--

1004
01:19:23,859 --> 01:19:25,759
The new-- n-new--
new night watchman.

1005
01:19:25,861 --> 01:19:27,761
You showed me
around here.

1006
01:19:27,863 --> 01:19:29,763
You know what
time it is?

1007
01:19:29,865 --> 01:19:32,026
Inspector Cray, please.
Well, where'd he go?

1008
01:19:32,134 --> 01:19:34,227
The hospital?
Alone?

1009
01:19:34,336 --> 01:19:38,102
<i>You remember the story you told</i>
<i>me about the night watchman</i>
<i>who did it with-- You know.</i>

1010
01:19:38,207 --> 01:19:40,767
- W-What year was it?
- The guy with the corpses?

1011
01:19:40,876 --> 01:19:44,107
- Yeah. Yeah.
- Before I started, in the late '60s.

1012
01:19:44,213 --> 01:19:46,738
- Do you remember his name?
- No.

1013
01:19:46,849 --> 01:19:48,942
And what happened to him?

1014
01:19:49,051 --> 01:19:51,315
- Nothin'.
- What?

1015
01:19:51,420 --> 01:19:56,255
The embarrassment.
The hospital couldn't press charges.

1016
01:19:56,358 --> 01:20:00,920
No. I guess he's out there
somewhere.

1017
01:20:09,872 --> 01:20:11,772
Where is she?

1018
01:20:48,077 --> 01:20:50,602
<i>[ Phone Ringing ]</i>

1019
01:20:52,748 --> 01:20:57,048
<i>[ Ringing Continues ]</i>

1020
01:20:57,152 --> 01:20:59,620
Cray.

1021
01:20:59,788 --> 01:21:03,451
[ Ringing Continues ]

1022
01:21:03,559 --> 01:21:09,020
<i>[ Ringing Continues ]</i>

1023
01:21:11,467 --> 01:21:14,197
Hello?

1024
01:21:14,303 --> 01:21:16,965
Hello?

1025
01:21:17,072 --> 01:21:20,530
Martin, it's
Inspector Cray.

1026
01:21:20,643 --> 01:21:22,543
We have
a situation here.

1027
01:21:26,548 --> 01:21:29,039
- Yeah?
-Joyce has been murdered.

1028
01:21:31,387 --> 01:21:33,287
Oh.

1029
01:21:33,389 --> 01:21:36,586
We have to talk.

1030
01:21:36,692 --> 01:21:39,718
Well, I'll, uh--
I'll come down to the station.

1031
01:21:39,828 --> 01:21:42,922
We really have to get
to the bottom of this.

1032
01:21:43,032 --> 01:21:45,796
I think it might be better
if I pick you up.

1033
01:21:47,670 --> 01:21:49,570
<i>Martin?</i>

1034
01:21:52,708 --> 01:21:56,838
- Are you still there?
- I-I'd prefer to come down to the station.

1035
01:21:56,945 --> 01:21:59,846
<i>[ Cray ]</i>
<i>I'll come and get you.</i>

1036
01:22:01,817 --> 01:22:06,015
<i>Tell me something, Martin. Are you still</i>
<i>gonna maintain your innocence?</i>

1037
01:22:07,356 --> 01:22:11,053
- Yeah.
- Who else could it be, Martin?

1038
01:22:11,160 --> 01:22:15,426
<i>The killing has to stop, Martin.</i>
<i>Don't you want it to stop?</i>

1039
01:22:15,531 --> 01:22:18,193
Maybe I could talk
to Deputy Inspector Bill.

1040
01:22:18,300 --> 01:22:20,200
Why wouldn't you
want to talk to me?

1041
01:22:25,007 --> 01:22:27,567
You're under arrest,
Martin.

1042
01:22:27,676 --> 01:22:30,270
Would you please
put this on your desk?

1043
01:22:53,135 --> 01:22:55,933
[ Gasps ]

1044
01:22:56,038 --> 01:22:58,006
We have all the time
in the world...

1045
01:22:58,107 --> 01:23:01,975
- to wait for your confession, Martin.
- [ Sobbing ]

1046
01:23:02,077 --> 01:23:04,477
All the time
in the world.

1047
01:23:12,821 --> 01:23:15,585
I want you to do me
a favor, Martin.

1048
01:23:17,326 --> 01:23:20,261
- [ Whimpering ]
- Hit me.

1049
01:23:20,362 --> 01:23:22,296
- What?
<i>- Come on, come on.</i>

1050
01:23:22,397 --> 01:23:24,888
Hit me.

1051
01:23:25,000 --> 01:23:27,161
How much more
can you take?

1052
01:23:27,269 --> 01:23:29,897
<i>You know what they're going to do</i>
<i>to you, Martin?</i>

1053
01:23:30,005 --> 01:23:32,667
They're going
to snuff you out, like a bug...

1054
01:23:32,775 --> 01:23:35,744
<i>hitting a windshield.</i>

1055
01:23:35,844 --> 01:23:38,074
You're going
to die anyway, Martin.

1056
01:23:38,180 --> 01:23:40,671
Don't you know
that you're going to die?

1057
01:23:40,783 --> 01:23:43,149
Now, come on, Martin.
You've got to do something.

1058
01:23:43,252 --> 01:23:45,516
Protect yourself.
Save yourself.

1059
01:23:45,621 --> 01:23:47,521
Martin, this is
your last chance.

1060
01:23:47,623 --> 01:23:52,526
<i>Do something!</i>
<i>Or I'll take your girlfriend's eyes.</i>

1061
01:24:04,239 --> 01:24:06,139
Martin?

1062
01:24:12,147 --> 01:24:14,479
Martin!

1063
01:24:23,625 --> 01:24:26,355
He's gone mad! Get in the hall!
Get in the hall!

1064
01:24:28,230 --> 01:24:30,289
<i>No!</i>

1065
01:24:31,400 --> 01:24:33,994
No! Katherine!

1066
01:24:35,304 --> 01:24:37,204
No!

1067
01:24:40,776 --> 01:24:42,869
I shouldn't be
telling you this,

1068
01:24:42,978 --> 01:24:46,607
but she wrote his name
before she died.

1069
01:24:46,715 --> 01:24:49,206
I know. Deputy Inspector Bill
told me.

1070
01:24:49,318 --> 01:24:52,515
Deputy Inspector Bill
told you?

1071
01:24:53,622 --> 01:24:56,147
That's highly unorthodox.

1072
01:25:04,633 --> 01:25:07,067
Ahhh!

1073
01:25:11,707 --> 01:25:14,608
I'm very glad
you told me this.

1074
01:25:16,345 --> 01:25:18,245
This changes everything.

1075
01:25:25,654 --> 01:25:28,987
All right, let's go through this
one more time.

1076
01:25:29,091 --> 01:25:32,424
Why didn't you call
from Joyce's apartment?

1077
01:25:38,934 --> 01:25:41,801
<i>'Cause the murderer</i>
<i>was still there.</i>

1078
01:25:41,870 --> 01:25:43,770
The murderer
was still there?

1079
01:25:43,872 --> 01:25:45,772
<i>She was already dead.</i>

1080
01:25:45,874 --> 01:25:47,774
She was already dead?

1081
01:25:47,876 --> 01:25:51,243
<i>- She hadn't written anything, so--</i>
- Yes?

1082
01:25:51,346 --> 01:25:54,747
<i>Someone else</i>
<i>must have written it.</i>

1083
01:25:54,850 --> 01:25:57,546
<i>Trying to frame</i>
<i>Martin, right?</i>

1084
01:25:57,653 --> 01:26:00,451
Trying to frame Martin?
Yes.

1085
01:26:04,393 --> 01:26:06,793
<i>Where are we?</i>

1086
01:26:13,902 --> 01:26:16,097
Interesting theory.

1087
01:26:16,204 --> 01:26:19,503
<i>What do we do now?</i>

1088
01:26:46,535 --> 01:26:49,436
## [ Whistling
"This Old Man" ]

1089
01:26:56,578 --> 01:26:58,876
## [ Continues Whistling ]

1090
01:27:03,652 --> 01:27:06,177
<i>- [ Katherine Screaming ]</i>
- Katherine!

1091
01:27:06,288 --> 01:27:08,188
Katherine!

1092
01:27:09,858 --> 01:27:11,758
<i>- [ Katherine Screams ]</i>
- Katherine!

1093
01:27:11,860 --> 01:27:14,226
<i>- [ Screaming ]</i>
- Katherine!

1094
01:27:16,832 --> 01:27:21,064
<i>Katherine!</i>

1095
01:27:21,169 --> 01:27:23,069
Katherine!

1096
01:27:34,950 --> 01:27:38,750
<i>Martin, I'm waiting.</i>

1097
01:27:38,854 --> 01:27:40,947
<i>[ Bat Clatters To Floor ]</i>

1098
01:27:41,056 --> 01:27:42,318
<i>[James ]</i>
<i>Martin!</i>

1099
01:27:43,358 --> 01:27:45,519
- Martin!
- Martin!

1100
01:27:45,627 --> 01:27:48,255
<i>[ Indistinct Radio Chatter ]</i>

1101
01:27:48,363 --> 01:27:51,264
<i>[ Pounding ]</i>

1102
01:27:55,570 --> 01:27:57,470
Hey, hey, I was worried
about you.

1103
01:27:57,572 --> 01:28:00,200
- He knocked me out and escaped.
- Something's wrong.

1104
01:28:00,308 --> 01:28:03,300
Nothing's wrong.
Who's this?

1105
01:28:03,412 --> 01:28:05,642
This is James.

1106
01:28:08,216 --> 01:28:10,684
- Where's Katherine?
- How should I know?

1107
01:28:12,254 --> 01:28:15,621
Her bike's outside.
She must be in here somewhere.

1108
01:28:15,724 --> 01:28:18,693
Well, she's not
in here. He, uh--

1109
01:28:22,097 --> 01:28:24,622
He probably
took her with him.

1110
01:28:28,170 --> 01:28:30,035
Martin!

1111
01:28:31,106 --> 01:28:33,006
Martin!

1112
01:28:40,916 --> 01:28:43,407
[ Screaming ]

1113
01:28:43,518 --> 01:28:45,418
Help us!

1114
01:28:51,660 --> 01:28:53,560
[ Panting ]

1115
01:29:00,602 --> 01:29:03,264
<i>Listen, take him</i>
<i>to the station.</i>

1116
01:29:03,371 --> 01:29:05,737
I'll take one last look atJoyce.
I'll meet you there.

1117
01:29:08,477 --> 01:29:11,571
Wait a minute.
Why would they try to escape?

1118
01:29:11,680 --> 01:29:13,705
Take it easy.

1119
01:29:19,154 --> 01:29:21,679
Handcuff him.

1120
01:29:22,791 --> 01:29:24,884
What?

1121
01:29:24,993 --> 01:29:26,893
You're under arrest
for suspicion of murder.

1122
01:29:35,303 --> 01:29:37,601
I don't understand this.
This is bullshit.

1123
01:29:37,706 --> 01:29:39,799
You have some
doubts too. Tell him!

1124
01:29:39,908 --> 01:29:42,069
Doubts?

1125
01:29:46,615 --> 01:29:49,812
Doubts about what,
Deputy Inspector Bill?

1126
01:29:51,586 --> 01:29:53,486
Nothing.

1127
01:29:54,689 --> 01:29:58,147
[ Groaning ]

1128
01:30:04,733 --> 01:30:08,601
I don't like it when you keep things
from me, Deputy Inspector Bill.

1129
01:30:11,106 --> 01:30:13,870
I've always encouraged you
to have your own ideas...

1130
01:30:13,975 --> 01:30:16,000
and share them,
haven't I?

1131
01:30:17,345 --> 01:30:19,438
Yeah. It's nothing.
He's babbling.

1132
01:30:19,548 --> 01:30:21,516
You said you felt
something was wrong.

1133
01:30:21,616 --> 01:30:23,743
Well, something is
definitely wrong.

1134
01:30:23,852 --> 01:30:25,752
Take him away.

1135
01:30:52,280 --> 01:30:54,180
[ Spits ]

1136
01:30:59,154 --> 01:31:02,555
<i>[ Alarm Bell Ringing ]</i>

1137
01:31:05,060 --> 01:31:07,460
<i>[ Alarm Continues ]</i>

1138
01:31:23,278 --> 01:31:25,143
[ Sharp Groan ]

1139
01:31:29,351 --> 01:31:31,251
No!

1140
01:31:34,089 --> 01:31:36,216
<i>- [ Davies Groans ]</i>
- No!

1141
01:31:36,324 --> 01:31:40,192
<i>[ Alarm Continues ]</i>

1142
01:31:52,340 --> 01:31:54,240
[ Panting ]

1143
01:32:02,450 --> 01:32:04,509
Have you ever
been killed before?

1144
01:32:09,791 --> 01:32:12,191
I'll be back in a minute.

1145
01:32:12,294 --> 01:32:14,922
[ Screaming ]
No!

1146
01:32:15,030 --> 01:32:17,624
<i>[ Alarm Continues ]</i>

1147
01:32:22,971 --> 01:32:25,735
<i>[ Alarm Bell</i>
<i>Stops Ringing ]</i>

1148
01:32:31,446 --> 01:32:35,212
No. No. No.

1149
